<TITLE> OIC chief due Tuesday </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Nov 02 (bdnews24.com)--Secretary-general of the Organisation of the Islamic Conference Ekmeleddin Ihsanoglu will arrive in Dhaka on Tuesday on a three-day visit, says a press release issued by the OIC office in Jeddah. Ihsanoglu will have talks with president Zillur Rahman, prime minister Sheikh Hasina and other high-ranking officials, says the statement issued by Dr Abdelhamid Salhi of the OIC's information department. It said the OIC chief would also attend a convocation of the Islamic University of Technology in Gazipur. The statement says the secretary-general comes at the invitation of foreign minister Dipu Moni. Ihsanoglu will also visit Dhaka University and deliver a talk on "OIC's Vision Meeting the Challenges for the 21st Century", the statement further says.
